Plan for Adding a Search Bar to Resume Viewer

1. Add HTML for Search Bar:
- Create an input field at the top of the HTML document with placeholder text "Search anything...".
Style the Search Bar:

2. Use CSS to style the search bar to float right with a top margin.
- Define a CSS class .highlight to highlight matched text with a red background and bold font.
JavaScript for Search Functionality:

3. Get the search input and resumes container by their IDs.
- Add an event listener to the search input for user input.
- When typing, get the search term, convert to lowercase, and trim spaces.
- Select all relevant elements in the resumes.
- Loop through each element, split its text by the search term, and rebuild with highlights.
- If itâ€™s the first match, remember the element and scroll it into view smoothly.